# CALIBRATION MEASUREMENTS — drift log

Each block below is one run of `calibration-ruler.sh` (the frozen ruler, v1.0).
The instrument is held constant; only the node fields should move between runs.
To read drift: `diff` any two blocks. M0 is the fixed reference point.

Ruler discipline: shell-only, single vantage. Do not edit the ruler between
measurements without bumping its version — a changed ruler measures nothing.

